The naval officer of gigantic stature<note>Sydney Smith Haldimand Dickens (1847-72), CD’s fifth son, about whose small size CD often joked. Served as midshipman on H.M.S. <hi rend="italic">Orlando</hi>, 6 Dec 61 to 12 May 64; joined H.M.S. <hi rend="italic">Pelican</hi>, June 64.</note> who will (I hope) present this note to you, is my son, bearing a high character in the service. He is naturally desirous to shake hands with a famous writer who is his father’s friend. And I know you will good naturedly gratify him if you can.
